To build a fresh arch-linux image just run "build.sh"
The new image will be found in "data/arch-strap.latest.tar"
You can then import it in docker to test using
    - docker import `readlink data/arch-strap.latest.tar` ioriomauro/arch-strap-test
    - docker run --rm -ti ioriomauro/arch-strap-test /bin/bash
Once satisfied, You can compress the archive, tag and push the image wherever You want,
and clean You docker db with
    - docker rmi $(docker images -q -f dangling=true)
